                        <provenance type="found">Discovered during excavation in <date>1934</date>, lying <q>'lengthwise along the passage'</q> of a souterrain, <q>'just under the
surface soil, on top of the filling stones'</q>(Mongey 1935, 267). A fragment with ogham-like marks was also found and read by <persName><surname>Macalister</surname></persName> (1935, 149) as BHOH or BHOH. He dismissed it as <q>'of no epigraphic importance'</q> (1949, 278 including sketch). It was reportedly sent to the museum with the larger stone but its current whereabouts is unknown.</provenance>
